Gdańsk University of Technology
The Gdańsk University of Technology is a higher education institution that oversees studies and student procedures, providing various study programs and academic services. It has a student government and a students' parliament, which plays a role in the decision-making process. The university is responsible for conducting studies, admissions, and student rights, while also defining the rules and organization of studies.

The institution has specific rules and regulations for student registration, scholarships, academic achievements, and the diploma process. It oversees the diploma examination process and has rules for thesis validation, ensuring that students receive a certificate of completion after meeting the necessary requirements. The university governs the academic policies and regulations, providing education and study opportunities for students.

Gdańsk
Gdańsk is the city where the university is located.<SEP>Gdańsk is the location of the university.

data.content:
individual student account in Moja PG system
An individual student account in the ‘Moja PG’ system contains information on the student’s course of studies and current status.

individual organization of studies
Individual organization of studies allows for individual selection of subjects and timetable, adapted to the student’s particular scientific interests or current situation.

individual research studies
Individual research studies involve the implementation of scientific research as part of research projects.

individual inter-disciplinary studies
Individual inter-disciplinary studies involve research projects with at least two fields and allow for obtaining a diploma in more than one field of study.

subject card
A subject card includes description of a subject, including subject assumptions, objectives, learning outcomes, ECTS credits, prerequisites, forms of classes, methods, and means of verifying learning outcomes.

course
A course is a program in a field of study, pursued by students commencing studies in a particular academic year.

semester
Semester is a period of study within the academic year.

academic year
Academic year consists of two semesters: winter and summer.<SEP>The academic year starts on October 1st and ends on September 30th.

study program
Study program can be conducted in full-time or part-time mode.<SEP>Study program is a set of courses and requirements for students.

lectures

classes

laboratory classes

seminars

distance education methods and techniques
Distance education methods and techniques are used for teaching.

Rector
Rector is the head of the university, responsible for its administration and academic policies.<SEP>Rector is the superior of all university students.<SEP>The Rector is the head of the university and responsible for making regulations on study plans and curriculums.<SEP>The rector is the person authorized to make decisions about student registration and removal.

Dean
The Dean is a university administrator responsible for overseeing various aspects of academic and administrative matters within a faculty. As the head of a faculty, they are responsible for making decisions on student registration, academic matters, and handling grade changes. They also have the authority to decide on the date and time of the diploma examination, appoint examination committee members, and award diplomas. Furthermore, they are responsible for academic decisions and regulations, overseeing the diploma process, and making decisions regarding examinations and credits. Additionally, they are in charge of approving individual study plans, making decisions on student progress, and handling student reinstatement and leaves.

Student Government
Student Government of Gdańsk University of Technology is responsible for student affairs.<SEP>The Student Government is consulted on university procedures and guidelines for diploma theses.<SEP>The Student Government is responsible for providing opinions on academic matters.<SEP>The Student Government is responsible for representing students and their interests within the university.

Student
The Student is an individual who is enrolled in academic studies, pursuing studies at the university, attending classes, and responsible for their own learning and academic progress. To be eligible for the diploma examination, a student is required to complete all semesters, including obligatory training courses and internships. Students have rights and responsibilities within the university, and are subject to its rules and regulations, while also receiving a certificate of completion upon fulfilling their academic obligations.
